main event: On 6 February 1952, two unidentified visual objects were reported observed in the sky over El Paso, Texas.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, silver in color, and traveling at a high speed at about 20,000 feet altitude., The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes., The Control Tower at El Paso International Airport reported no unidentified objects observed during that time., No confirmation from other reliable sources was available, leading to no further investigation by the office., An investigation into the photographs of unidentified aerial objects has been requested by the Directorate of Intelligence of the USAF.
